-- Belgium’s Frederik Van Lierde Wins Ironman World Championship
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-10-13T04:17:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-13/belgium-s-frederik-van-lierde-wins-ironman-world-championship.html
Belgium ’s Frederik Van Lierde won
the Ironman World Championship with the eighth fastest time in
the 35-year history of the event.  Van Lierde, 34, who placed third last year, completed the
triathlon in eight hours, 12 minutes and 29 seconds yesterday in
Kailua-Kona,  Hawaii .  He was 25th after the 2.4-mile (3.9 kilometers) swim, moved
up to fourth place in the 112-mile bike ride and then ran into
first place with just under 10 miles left in the 26.2-mile
marathon.  Australian Luke McKenzie was second in the men’s
competition, finishing the competition in eight hours, 15
minutes and 19 seconds.  Australia’s Mirinda Carfrae was the first woman to complete
the course, finishing in eight hours, 52 minutes and 14 seconds,
with  Great Britain ’s Rachel Joyce second in eight hours, 57
minutes and 28 seconds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
